    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://jgoldfar.github.io/tags/julia-lang/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 02 Jan 2019 14:29:00 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jgoldfar.github.io/tags/julia-lang/</guid>
      <description>Julia is a dynamic, optionally typed, high-performance, open-source programming language.
While initially devised as a language and runtime for scientific computing a-la MATLAB, it promises to be the ultimate prototyping-to-production language: performance akin to a traditional compiled language, but with programming productivity (enabled by the flexible, expressive, and dynamic nature of the language itself) akin to Python or R. Julia is an excellent &amp;ldquo;glue&amp;rdquo; language, enabling the utilization of codes written in anything from C and C++ to Python and R in a coherent way.</description>
    </item>
    
